Package uniol.apt.util

Various reusable utility functions.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IEquivalenceRelation<E>
    Implementations of this interface can decide if two objects are equivalent to each other in some sense.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractEquivalenceRelation<E>
    Base class for equivalence relations.
    DebugUtil
    Helper functions for having debug output.
    DifferentPairsIterable<E>
    Iterable for iterating over all pairs of different elements of a given collection.
    DomainEquivalenceRelation<E>
    An equivalence relation where the basic set over which it is defined is explicitly given.
    EquivalenceRelation<E>
    Instances of this class represent an equivalence relation over an unknown set.
    MathTools
    Some methods for mathematical calculations like gcd and modulo.
    Pair<X,Y>
    Represents a Pair of elements.
    PowerSet<E>
    Calculate the power set of a collection.
    PowerSet.BitSetIterable
    Iterable that creates BitSetIterator instances.
    PowerSet.BitSetIterator
    Iterator that iterates through all possible BitSets of a given length.
    PowerSet.PowerSetIterator<E>
    Iterator that produces the power set of a given list.
    SpanningTree<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>
    Calculate a spanning tree of a graph based on a breadth-first search.
    StringComparator
    A comparator on strings that is useful for sorting numbered names.
